Package soot.jimple.infoflow.nativeCallHandler

Interface INativeCallHandler

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractNativeCallHandler, BackwardNativeCallHandler, DefaultNativeCallHandler
    public interface INativeCallHandler
    The NativeCallHandler defines the taint propagation behavior for native code, as we cannot analyze these methods

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      Set<Abstraction> getTaintedValues​(soot.jimple.Stmt call, Abstraction source, soot.Value[] params)
      Returns the set of tainted values for a given call to native code, a given tainted value and the list of passed arguments
      void initialize​(InfoflowManager manager)
      This method is called before the taint propagation is started to give the native call handler the chance to initialize required components once Soot is running, but before it is queried for the first time.
      void shutdown()
      Tells the native call handler that it can free all resources it has allocated at initialization time
      boolean supportsCall​(soot.jimple.Stmt call)
      Checks whether this handler is able to handle the given call, i.e., has an explicit model for it

    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        void initialize​(InfoflowManager manager)
        This method is called before the taint propagation is started to give the native call handler the chance to initialize required components once Soot is running, but before it is queried for the first time. Note that this method is guaranteed to be called only once and only by a single thread.
        Parameters:
        manager - The manager object providing access to the data flow solver processing the IFDS edges and the interprocedural control flow graph

      • getTaintedValues

        Set<Abstraction> getTaintedValues​(soot.jimple.Stmt call,
                                  Abstraction source,
                                  soot.Value[] params)
        Returns the set of tainted values for a given call to native code, a given tainted value and the list of passed arguments
        Parameters:
        call - the statement which contains the call to the native code
        source - the incoming taint value
        params - list of arguments
        Returns:
        the resulting set of taints

      • supportsCall

        boolean supportsCall​(soot.jimple.Stmt call)
        Checks whether this handler is able to handle the given call, i.e., has an explicit model for it
        Parameters:
        call - The call site to check
        Returns:
        True if this native call handler has an explicit model for the given call site, otherwise false

      • shutdown

        void shutdown()
        Tells the native call handler that it can free all resources it has allocated at initialization time
